<br>
I'm still half asleep this morning so my brain isn't working enough to begin jotting down my items for awards here and now, but I plan to put up a post in the guild roundtable for some ideas and suggestions from everyone else... <br>
<br>
I have, however, if you approve, come up with a bit of a plan... Say a week (Or two if you think we need more time) to get a list of Awards... Then another week to start choosing who to give the Awards out to... That would give us about two weeks and then we can plan an event to make a ceremony out of giving these awards... Anyway that's my basic ideas for the arrangement, I figure we can do the Awards once each month, like for example an employee of the month kind of thing... Someone gets the award for kindness soul (Again for example) then that person would hold it for a month and then pass it on the following month in the ceremony to the one that gets it next... Also had some thoughts that we could also do some of the Awards as permanent and those are the ones that would probably be easiest to keep up with as far as putting them under our names when we post... Plus I'm trying to think of ways to make this ceremony not only monthly, but exciting enough that everyone will want to come... <br>
<br>
This is just a start and merely my ideas Siper... Do let me know if perhaps you have come up with anything different... Just figured it was about time we began getting the awards deal going...<br>
